    <article title="Cirrhosis">
      <p class="intro">
        Cirrhosis is the end stage for any chronic liver disease. In the United States, 4.9 million people are living with the build-up of hardened scar tissue in the liver called cirrhosis. The numbers have been increasing.
      </p>

